{
  "text": "In our experiment, renalase protein levels decreased in the kidney of trained rats, while its mRNA increased. [CITATION_1] , recently showed that the constrictive response of renal resistance arteries to norepinephrine in rats increased following exercise training. In a study by [CITATION_2] , the authors showed that endurance training exacerbates the fall in GFR and renal blood flow following acute kidney injury. The results of [CITATION_3] , showed that endurance training reduced vasoconstriction during the orthostatic reaction, and could contrib- Fig. 6 . Serum levels of renalase do not change after endurance training or acute exercise. Timepoints include: pre-exercise for trained and untrained rats (Tpre and UTpre, respectively), immediately after exercise (T0h, UT0h), and three hours post exercise (T3h, UT3h).",
